summary: sorry if you've been asked about this before but do you think there'll be a dance of dragons between jon and D? if yes, do you...
question: sorry if you've been asked about this before but do you think there'll be a dance of dragons between jon and D? if yes, do you think it'll be after they deal with the NK or before? i just really wanna watch these two fight to death sksksks
answer:
Same.

The Night King will die in the first half of the season and then we’ll have a Dance of Dragons. Jon has elements of Aegon VI’s character and he has a connection with Dany’s dragon that other characters don’t have. Dany will go to war with Aegon in the books and will likely kill him (along with everyone in KL including my Martell faves) so it makes sense that she goes to war with Jon in the show. HBO has put emphasis on Jon as the heir and Emilia said that Dany has been working to win the Iron Throne for years, I doubt she’ll be happy to learn she has a competitor. Jon might die from this fight so you might get your wish anon

summary: “her very last scene” does not equal “last scene of the show”  sansa isn’t gonna be on the iron throne. its not gonna be sansa...
body:
“her very last scene” does not equal “last scene of the show”

sansa isn’t gonna be on the iron throne. its not gonna be sansa and jon’s kids.

 its most likely gonna be a shot of her ruling winterfell. we’ve already seen scenes of sansa acting as lady of winterfell, so if she really has the storyboard hanging in her house, nobody would take a second look at a picture of her ruling  winterfell because they would assume its a scene we already saw. 

its gonna be a shot of her in winterfell.

summary: If Sansa does end up back in King's Landing for one reason or a another, all I want is for her to get back the doll Ned gave her...
question: If Sansa does end up back in King's Landing for one reason or a another, all I want is for her to get back the doll Ned gave her before his death. It must still be in her old room before she fled.
answer: I have to be honest with you anon, I don’t care for that doll. It’s a sign of how little Ned cared to know about his 13 year old daughter that he made her a doll while she was angry about her wolf’s death.
